plicationContextRunner, the standard lightweight way to exercise Spring Boot autoconfiguration without starting an external service.\"}],\"agent_guidance\":\"No Docker image, API key, environment variable, or system property is needed. Tests should use an in-memory stub ChatModel and Spring Boot context setup rather than contacting an AI provider. For 2.0.0, avoid the removed spring.ai.chat.client.tool-calling.stream-tool-call-responses property and the absent isStreamToolCallResponses() accessor; the remaining tool-calling properties are enabled and advisor-order.\",\"risks\":[\"If generated tests are copied from the 2.0.0-RC2 scaffold unchanged, they can fail javac because stream-tool-call-responses is not present in 2.0.0.\",\"The optional micrometer-tracing-specific branch is not covered by this baseline setup unless the workflow deliberately adds micrometer-tracing and tests that path.\"]}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0d61816162e90a94016a402c1c4e6c8194a9e1392dca657527\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1934, "output": 964, "cacheRead": 33280, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 36178, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782590485969, "responseId": "resp_0d61816162e90a94016a402c168a388194b8a9a442b07140f0"}}
